CatDescriptText: Mr. James Timbrell, 140 S. Orchard Street, Berwick, Pa, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1958, pg. 5 with question: "Do you think that the city needs a fair housing ordinance?" answer reads: "Generally speaking, I would say that if the resale value of properties isn't damaged by the inclusion of race, creed or color, I would say that it is all right. But if the value deteriorates because of that, I would oppose it."
